# Bookkeeping standards

## Method

- Default: **accrual basis** per `company/profile.md`.
- Double-entry implied: every debit has a matching credit in journal entries.

## Chart of accounts

- Use numeric ranges: 1000 assets, 2000 liabilities, 3000 equity, 4000 revenue, 5000–6000 COGS/expenses.
- New accounts → add to `bookkeeping/chart-of-accounts/accounts.csv` before use.

## Journal format (CSV)

Required columns: `date,account_code,account_name,debit,credit,description,source_file,period`

## Naming

- Files: `YYYY-MM-DD_entity_short-description.ext`
- Period folders: `YYYY-MM` under reports and reconciliations.

## Reconciliation

- Monthly bank rec in `banking/reconciliations/YYYY-MM.md` or `.csv`.
- Match: statement ending balance = book balance ± outstanding items.
- Unmatched items >30 days → flag in report notes.

## Capitalization

- Expense items under **$500** (unless `company/profile.md` says otherwise) unless part of a single asset or clear long-life item.
- Ambiguous → log in `company/decision-log.md` and ask owner.

## Reports

- P&L and balance sheet snapshots go in `reports/YYYY-MM/` with `generated_on` date in header.
